Troubleshooting Tips
Import Errors
If cryptography modules fail to import:

pip3 install --upgrade cryptography
python3 -m pip install cryptography --user
Message Too Large for RSA
RSA encryption fails with large messages. Solutions:

Keep RSA messages under 190 bytes (2048-bit key)
Use hybrid encryption for large data
Split into chunks (not recommended)
Key File Permissions
If key files have permission issues:

chmod 600 *.pem *.key
ls -la *.pem *.key
Decryption Failures
Common causes:

Using wrong key for decryption
Corrupted ciphertext
Mismatched encryption/decryption methods
Key not initialized before use
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated fundamental cryptographic techniques using Python. You implemented symmetric encryption (AES) for fast bulk data encryption, asymmetric encryption (RSA) for secure key exchange and digital signatures, and hybrid encryption combining both approaches.

Key takeaways:

Symmetric (AES): Fast, efficient, requires secure key distribution
Asymmetric (RSA): Slower, enables secure key exchange, supports signatures
Hybrid: Industry standard combining both methods
Real-world: TLS/SSL, PGP, and secure messaging use these techniques
